{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2022-1716","published":"2022-06-17T11:03:53Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:17:29.336208Z","upstream":["CVE-2021-3507","CVE-2021-3611"],"summary":"qemu security update","details":"QEMU is a FAST! processor emulator using dynamic translation to achieve good emulation speed.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nA heap buffer overflow was found in the floppy disk emulator of QEMU up to 6.0.0 (including). It could occur in fdctrl_transfer_handler() in hw/block/fdc.c while processing DMA read data transfers from the floppy drive to the guest system. A privileged guest user could use this flaw to crash the QEMU process on the host resulting in DoS scenario, or potential information leakage from the host memory.(CVE-2021-3507)\r\n\r\nA stack overflow vulnerability was found in the Intel HD Audio device (intel-hda) of QEMU. A malicious guest could use this flaw to crash the QEMU process on the host, resulting in a denial of service condition. The highest threat from this vulnerability is to system availability. This flaw affects QEMU versions prior to 7.0.0.(CVE-2021-3611)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"qemu","ecosystem":"openEuler:20.03-LTS-SP1","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/qemu&distro=openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"4.1.0-66.oe1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["qemu-block-rbd-4.1.0-66.oe1.aarch64.rpm","qemu-guest-agent-4.1.0-66.oe1.aarch64.rpm","qemu-block-curl-4.1.0-66.oe1.aarch64.rpm","qemu-img-4.1.0-66.oe1.aarch64.rpm","qemu-debuginfo-4.1.0-66.oe1.aarch64.rpm","qemu-4.1.0-66.oe1.aarch64.rpm","qemu-block-iscsi-4.1.0-66.oe1.aarch64.rpm","qemu-debugsource-4.1.0-66.oe1.aarch64.rpm","qemu-block-ssh-4.1.0-66.oe1.aarch64.rpm"],"noarch":["qemu-help-4.1.0-66.oe1.noarch.rpm"],"src":["qemu-4.1.0-66.oe1.src.rpm"],"x86_64":["qemu-debuginfo-4.1.0-66.oe1.x86_64.rpm","qemu-guest-agent-4.1.0-66.oe1.x86_64.rpm","qemu-block-curl-4.1.0-66.oe1.x86_64.rpm","qemu-seabios-4.1.0-66.oe1.x86_64.rpm","